SIMPLE: intumescence
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intumescence
<hw>In`tu*mes"cence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>intumescence</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or process of swelling or enlarging; also,
the state of being swollen; expansion; tumidity; especially, the
swelling up of bodies under the action of heat.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>intumescence</qex> of nations.</q>
<rj><qau>Johnson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Anything swollen or enlarged, as a tumor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intumescent</ent>⟦br⟧
